description: API unit and e2e test conventions
globs: apps/api/**/*.spec.ts, apps/api/test/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# API — Tests

## Unit specs (`*.service.spec.ts`)

- Mock `PrismaService` with `jest-mock-extended` (`mockDeep`).
- Reset mocks in `beforeEach`.
- Never hit the real database from unit specs.
- Config: `apps/api/jest.config.js`

## E2E specs (`test/e2e/*.e2e-spec.ts`)

- Use shared setup in `apps/api/test/setup/`:
  - `app-factory.ts` — NestJS test app
  - `db.ts` — test database helpers
  - `e2e-env.ts` — env overrides
  - `auth-helpers.ts` — JWT helpers
- Config: `apps/api/test/jest-e2e.config.js`
- Start test DB first: `pnpm docker:test-db`

## Naming

- Unit: `<feature>.service.spec.ts` next to the service.
- E2E: `<feature>.e2e-spec.ts` under `apps/api/test/e2e/`.

## Running

- Unit: `pnpm test:api` or `pnpm --filter api test -- <pattern>`
- E2E: `pnpm test:api:e2e`
- Coverage: `pnpm test:api:cov`
